    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect timer processing in Registration Accept handling\n\n### Summary\nThe NR UE NAS module was not properly processing timer-related Information Elements (IEs) from Registration Accept messages, specifically T3512 (Periodic Registration Update Timer) and T3502 (Registration Attempt Timer). This led to protocol timer configurations with incorrect durations that violated 3GPP timing requirements.\n\nThe issue occurred both for protected and unprotected Registration Accept messages, as the timer IEs were being skipped during message parsing. The bug was particularly problematic when processing unprotected messages downstream of the security validation logic.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/NR_UE/nr_nas_msg.c`: \n  * Added `process_registration_accept_timers()` function to extract and process T3512 (IEI 0x5E) and T3502 (IEI 0x16) timer values from Registration Accept messages\n  * Modified `get_allowed_nssai()` to skip timer IEs since they're now processed separately\n  * Updated `handle_registration_accept()` to call the new timer processing function\n  * Added include for `GprsTimer.h` to access timer value decoding functions\n\n"
}